Use the standard library
This is how to find_closest_elements of numbers:
  Remember that closest_pair is []
  Remember that smallest_diff is nothing
  Remember that i is 0
  Do this numbers's length times:
    Remember that j is sum of i and 1
    Do this diff of numbers's length and j times:
      Remember that first is item i in numbers
      Remember that second is item j in numbers
      Remember that current_diff is abs of diff of first and second
      When smallest_diff is nothing, then:
        Remember that smallest_diff is current_diff
        Remember that closest_pair is [first, second]
      But, if not:
        When current_diff is less than smallest_diff, then:
          Remember that smallest_diff is current_diff
          Remember that closest_pair is [first, second]
        End when
      End when
      Increase j
    End do
    Increase i
  End do
  The answer is closest_pair
